What is Lighttpd?

	Lighttpd (pronounced "lighty") is a lightweight, fast, and efficient open-source web server software. It is designed to use minimal system resources while delivering high performance, making it ideal for low-memory or embedded systems.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

What is MariaDB?

	MariaDB is an open-source relational database management system (RDBMS) that serves as a drop-in replacement for MySQL. It was developed as a fork of MySQL after Oracle acquired MySQL, to ensure the database remains open-source and community-driven.

	MariaDB is widely used for storing, organizing, and managing data in structured formats. It is known for being fast, scalable, and highly reliable.


